  "text": "The opiate system may also play a role in posttraumatic stress disorder (PTSD). About half of the PTSD patients had an increased hormone response to naloxone, but the endocrine changes did not correlate with the severity of PTSD symptoms or with other standard psychiatric illness or other measures of psychological testing. In this subgroup, it is possible that there was an opiate-mediated hypersensitivity of the HPA axis [CITATION_1] . I n vitro studies of blood cells from patients with PTSD revealed an alteration of immune functioning in response to opiates, with Met-enkephalin increasing natural killer cell activity in patients with symptoms but not in normals [CITATION_2] .",
